727720f-b.text:
QUeens Boulevard, north side, east from Van Loon Street to Broadway showing in the foreoround of hoth vieus te former Association Hall (square building). It was oririnally the Baptist Vhurch, erected in 1809. At that time it was a one atory building. Beyond it are peaked roof hoses owned by A Proctor in 1873. At the corner of the ahove mentioned Boulevard and Broadway is the Higes Hotel of 1891.
March 1923
View 2: May 1929
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
